        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fail closed for CLI-backed /btw fallback",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #92168.\n\n- fail closed when `/btw` would otherwise fall back to direct provider auth for a model routed through a CLI runtime alias\n- preserve existing `/btw` direct fallback behavior for non-CLI/custom harnesses without side-question hooks\n- add regression coverage proving CLI-runtime alias models do not call direct provider auth or direct streaming\n\n## Verification\n\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/btw.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/btw.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose -t \"fails closed instead of using direct provider auth for CLI-runtime alias models|keeps the direct provider fallback for non-Codex harnesses without side-question hooks\"`\n- `git diff --check -- src/agents/btw.ts src/agents/btw.test.ts`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `/btw` no longer silently switches a CLI-runtime-backed model to direct provider auth/streaming when no side-question hook is available.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on Node/Vitest agent test lane.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/btw.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose` and the focused regression command listed above.\n\nEvidence after fix: full `src/agents/btw.test.ts` passed 34/34; focused regression proof passed 2/2.\n\nObserved result after fix: CLI-runtime alias models fail closed before `getApiKeyForModel`, provider stream registration, or direct `streamSimple`; non-CLI harness fallback remains available.\n\nWhat was not tested: no live Crabbox run was repeated after the patch; the fix is covered by targeted unit regression proof for the implicated `/btw` fallback path.\n",
        "branch": "fix/btw-cli-runtime-fail-closed",
